info.description: This API allows access to Cloud Manager programs, pipelines, and environments by an authorized technical account created through the Adobe I/O Console. The base url for this API is https://cloudmanager.adobe.io, e.g. to get the list of programs for an organization, you would make a GET request to https://cloudmanager.adobe.io/api/programs (with the correct set of headers as described below). This swagger file can be downloaded from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AdobeDocs/cloudmanager-api-docs/master/swagger-specs/api.yaml.

trigger.description: How should the execution be triggered. ON_COMMIT: each time a PR is available and the Pipeline is idle then a execution is triggered. MANUAL: triggerd through UI or API. SCHEDULE: recurring schedule (not yet implemented}

pipelinePhase.description: Describes a phase of a pipeline

repositoryId.description:
Identifier of the source repository. The code from this repository will be build at the start of this phase.
Mandatory if type=BUILD

branch.description:
Name of the tracked branch or a fully qualified git tag (e.g. refs/tags/v1).
 Assumed to be `master` if missing.

environmentId.description: Identifier of the target environment. Mandatory if type=DEPLOY

programId.description: Identifier of the program. Unique within the space.

pipelineId.description: Identifier of the pipeline. Unique within the space.

artifactsVersion.description: Version of the artifacts generated during this execution

user.description: AdobeID who started the pipeline. Empty for auto triggered builds

finishedAt.description: Date the execution reached a final state

pipelineExecutionStepState.description: Describes the status of a particular pipeline execution step for display purposes

override.description: Whether user override the failed metric
